# Backend Standards — TechyNews (Laravel 13)

## Service Layer Pattern
All business logic lives in `app/Services/`:
- `GeminiService` — AI text generation (Gemini API calls, with OpenRouter fallback)
- `NewsService` — RSS feed aggregation (TechCrunch, The Verge, Ars Technica, HN)
- `LlamaService` — Local Ollama fallback for AI calls (deprecated)
- `SocialMediaService` — Twitter/X API integration for auto-posting

## Controllers
- `PublicController` — Homepage, article show, search (cached, public)
- `DashboardController` — Studio page + Analytics (auth required)
- `ArticleController` — CRUD + publish + like
- `AiController` — AI generation endpoints (generate-ideas, generate-draft, studio-chat, etc.)
- `ScoutQueueController` — Scout agent queue management
- `AnalyticsController` — Public analytics endpoints
- `ChatController` — RAG copilot chat

## Eloquent Conventions
- Use `$fillable` arrays, never `$guarded = []`
- Cast JSON columns: `'tags' => 'array'`
- Store content as raw HTML string — never `json_encode()` HTML
- Use type hints on all method parameters and return types

## Error Handling (Mandatory)
- **ALWAYS** wrap external API calls (Gemini, OpenRouter, RSS) in try/catch
- **ALWAYS** log with context: `Log::error('Gemini API failed', ['model' => $model, 'error' => $e->getMessage()])`
- **ALWAYS** return structured JSON errors: `response()->json(['error' => $message], $statusCode)`
- **NEVER** catch and silently ignore exceptions
- **Fallback chain**: Gemini → OpenRouter → user-friendly error message

## Artisan Commands
- `news:generate-daily` — Daily automated article generation (scheduled 06:00)
- `article:fix-encoding` — Fix double-encoded HTML in DB
- `news:fetch-daily` — Legacy RSS fetch (deprecated)

## Environment Variables
- `GEMINI_API_KEY` — Required for AI generation
- `GEMINI_MODEL` — Model name (default: `gemini-2.0-flash`)
- `OPEN_ROUTER_API_KEY` — Fallback AI provider
- `OPEN_ROUTER_MODEL` — Fallback model name
- `DB_*` — MySQL production credentials

## Rate Limiting
- 10-second `sleep()` between consecutive Gemini API calls
- HTTP timeout: 60 seconds per request

## Testing Requirements
- Run `php artisan test` before every deploy
- Write tests for new service methods
- Test API endpoints with `curl` after deploy
